Parliament, Wednesday 16 October 2019 – Deputy President David Mabuza will provide oral replies to questions by Members of Parliament in the National Assembly (NA) tomorrow, 17 October. Section 92(2) of the Constitution obligates Cabinet Members to account to Parliament for the exercise of their powers and performance of their functions and Parliament utilises this opportunity to hold the Executive accountable.
	The six (6) questions to be answered by the Deputy President include: Meanwhile, the National Council of Provinces (NCOP) is scheduled to feature an oral question and answer session to the Governance Cluster 3 which comprises of the Minister of Co-operative Governance and Traditional Affairs; the Minister of Public Service and Administration; the Minister in the Presidency for Women, Youth and Persons with Disabilities; and the Minister in the Presidency.
	
	In terms of Rule 246(4), no more than six questions for oral reply may be put to a Minister in respect of any one government department on any particular day.
	
	For the full list of questions to Deputy President, please click:
	https://www.parliament.gov.za/storage/app/media/Docs/quest_pap/c73bf543-450f-4938-92b8-21e708a825d1.pdf
	
